list_variables.description: A list of pipeline objects that make up the pipeline. For more information about             pipeline objects and a description of each object, see Pipeline Object Reference in the               AWS Data Pipeline Developer Guide.
list_variables.name: PipelineObjects
list_variables.type: A list of AWS Data Pipeline       PipelineObjects

variables.description: Indicates whether to validate and start the pipeline or stop an active pipeline. By             default, the value is set to true.
variables.name: Activate

variables.description: A name for the pipeline. Because AWS CloudFormation assigns each new pipeline a unique                         identifier, you can use the same name for multiple pipelines that are                         associated with your AWS account.
variables.name: Name

variables.description: Defines the variables that are in the pipeline definition. For more                         information, see Creating                             a Pipeline Using Parameterized Templates in the                             AWS Data Pipeline Developer Guide.
variables.name: ParameterObjects

variables.description: Defines the values for the parameters that are defined in the               ParameterObjects property. For more information, see Creating a Pipeline Using Parameterized               Templates in the AWS Data Pipeline Developer Guide.
variables.name: ParameterValues

variables.description: A list of arbitrary tags (key-value pairs) to associate with the pipeline, which you                         can use to control permissions. For more information, see Controlling Access to                             Pipelines and Resources in the                             AWS Data Pipeline Developer Guide.
variables.name: PipelineTags
